Class StringMaps.FileSequences

  • java.lang.Object
    • StringMaps.FileSequences
  • Enclosing class:
    StringMaps

    private class StringMaps.FileSequences
extends java.lang.Object
    FileSequences contains only a constructor. This class contains the logic for parsing and storing the txt files as sequences in StringMaps.fileSequences and for StringMaps.hashMap

    • Constructor Detail

      • FileSequences

        private FileSequences(java.io.File file)
        Parses a given txt file. Logic breakdown:
        • Create a BufferedReader and parse the entire file line-by-line (appending a space after each line) and store in a object
        • Iterate through entire StringBuilder object, char-by-char, and remove all characters that aren't characters or digits or whitespace
        • Split the string by using //s+
        • Iterate through String array and combine strings based upon StringMaps.sequenceSize into a sequence. If this new sequence does not have a corresponding key in StringMaps.hashMap, then put a new entry into the map. If the key already exists, and the sequence is from a different file, add the filename to the list associated with the hashed value of the sequence (Key)
        • Store the list of sequences in sequences
        Parameters:
        file - is the txt file to parse.
